text: Épineux-le-Seguin is a former commune of 172 people (1999). It is found in the region Pays de la Loire in the Mayenne department in the northwest of France. On 1 January 2017, it was merged into the new commune of Val-du-Maine.Arrêté préfectoral 22 July 2016 == References == Category:Former communes in Mayenne
title: Épineux-le-Seguin
